    • Method Detail

      • getInputStream

        public InputStream getInputStream()
        Description copied from interface: BinaryContent
        Gets the input stream.

        Note that the binary from the InputStream can only be accessed once. Thus, when you call BinaryContent.getInputStream() and retrieve the InputStream object, it can only be used once to extract the content. If it is necessary that the bytes of the InputStream object are needed again, use the BinaryContent.getByteArray() method instead.

        Specified by:
        getInputStream in interface BinaryContent
        Returns:
        an input stream

      • getByteArray

        public byte[] getByteArray()
                    throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: BinaryContent
        Convenience method to attempt to read the contents of the InputStream into a byte array.

        Note that BinaryContent.getByteArray() should be idempotent if BinaryContent.getInputStream() has not been initially invoked.

        Specified by:

        Returns:
